# MD Burke Workshop — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# NEVER commit the actual .env file to Git.
#
# ─── HOW TO SET IN NETLIFY ────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Go to: Netlify Dashboard → Your Site → Site Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Click "Add a variable" for EACH variable below
# 3. Paste in the values from your Supabase project:
#    Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your Supabase project URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# Public anon key (safe to expose in client)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ⚠ WARNING: Do NOT add the service role key here.
# The service role key has admin access and must never be used client-side.
# If you need server-side operations, use Netlify Functions instead.
